-- KKR Plans to Combine BHP, Rio Tinto Diamond Assets, Times Says
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2012-04-15T12:17:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/kkr-plans-to-combine-bhp-rio-tinto-diamond-assets-times-says.html
KKR & Co. (KKR)  plans to combine the
diamond assets that  Rio Tinto Plc (RIO)  and  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  are
seeking to sell, the Sunday Times  reported , without saying where
it got the information.  KKR is leading bids in a $750 million auction of BHPâ€™s
Ekati diamond mine in Canada after other suitors, including
 Apollo Global Management LLC (APO)  and  Gem Diamonds Ltd. (GEMD) , dropped out
of the sales process, the newspaper said.  Harry Winston Diamond
Corp. (HW)  and Stornoway Diamond Corp. remain in the running, the
Sunday Times reported.  KKR appointed Brian Menell to advise on its plans,
according to the newspaper  A spokeswoman for KKR declined to comment when reached by
phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
